HEADWORD: Focalize
<hw>Fo"cal*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Focalized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Focalizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To bring
to a focus; to focus; to concentrate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Light is focalized in the eye, sound in the ear.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

